caption: This is my go-to place for Indian food. Everything I’ve ordered has always been hot, fresh, correct, and delicious! Can’t recommend them highly enough!
Ordered malai kofta.. the kofta was really hard and the cream was quite so so.. my first order here.. probably not gonna try again
Best veggie samosas in town, possibly even in the country

Our favorite local Indian spot - we have tried many Indian restaurants locally and keep coming back to Raj Darbar thanks to the Chana Masala, Veggie Samosas, and especially the garlic naan! (And also the fact it is just around the corner) Favorite naan we have found so far - we get 3-4 orders of it every time so we can have some with leftovers. Thanks Raj Darbar - we'll be ordering again soon!
So delicious!!! Have been craving butter chicken and this place filled my craving. Portions are big enough for two and food is very authentic. Found my new go to Indian place!

I used to work close to Raj Darbar before. The food is okay and I feel like it is a bit overpriced for the quantity of the food and the taste of the food as well. Just your average Indian food. But if you’re in a time crunch or if you really want to have some Indian food, go ahead and try it. I wouldn’t say I was disappointed but I wasn’t full 😅 I’m used to sharing with a friend and we definitely needed more food.

I sent my friends to this place with my warmest recommendations. I visit this place often. This recommendation is always successful. The meals are delicious and the team is welcoming and cooperative. Whenever we visit this place we have a splendid time.  highly recommended.
I really loved this place. I've had nothing but enjoyable experiences here and plan to keep visiting. The prices are fair for the quality of food.
Love this place. Food is always delicious

Whenever we come here the staff is so kind. A few times the owners came to speak to us at our table to get to know us. Not very many restaurants do that. We appreciate it and it’s part of the reason we come back. This picture is before covid and I haven’t visited since BUT papad and chutneys come to the table when you put your order in. We order our usual chicken tikka masala and lamb do piyaza(I like raj darbars lamb do piyaza the most. Lots of onions and peppers with tender lamb) dishes come with rice or naan, you choose. My mother in law always gets an eggplant dish here. Only thing is, when you order soda they give you a glass of ice and a can. But last I checked it’s BYOB so that makes up for it haha. Usually you can find this restaurant on Groupon but the prices are set typical of any Indian restaurant, not too expensive.
My new favorite place for Indian. Can't wait for things to open up again so we can visit in person. Great value for the portions when it comes to delivery.

WOW!!! Some of the best best best Indian food I have ever had. I ordered the chicken tikka Marsala spicy, amazing. The chicken was excellent quality. The flavor was outstanding - very spicy but flavorful. 10/10 would recommend eating here!!
Consistently delicious. My absolute go-to. Get the pakoras, you'll thank me.
The food was amazing and the staff was friendly. But on my way out, I noticed a cockroach climbing up one of the sofas, which freaked me out a little. Hence, I decided to take out one star.
Tasty, with comically tiny portions
They serve big portions and for reasonable pricing. super friendly staff. Keep it up.
One of my go-to places to grab some food. awesome location, well kept, and very good service. I recommend this place!

Be sure to order rice for delivery. Does not come with entrees. Food was fantastic but I had to whip out a piece of bread to Raj Dar bar the intensity. Wish menu was more clear in addition to saying a la carte.

At the moment  you step in that restaurant  the personel give you a pleasant feeling. Very courteous stuff, it is a nice place to  pass time with friends and colleagues or with your date. Excellent  cuisine, experienced  chief cook and stuff, modest  price and professional  service. Highly recommended.
Great food. Super friendly wait staff. They were great with our toddler.sharon was great!
The chicken korma is awesome!
The food is always ready when promised, and all of their lamb dishes are great

I celebrated my birthday last night in this fine place. Well we passed a awesome evening and the venue was absolutely one of the reasons for this happy event. The waiters  contributed in a graceful way, the food was yummy and my buddies were very  delighted. We shall definitely visit again for more joyful events. Thank you very much.

We love eating out. Yesterday we arrived in this superb restaurant which we didn’t know before. We spent a beautiful time there with fine food and a nice stuff and an impressive chief cook. We put this restaurant in our list  and we shall certainly come back soon. We deeply recommend.
Best Indian food in Chicago!!
Sorry...chicken tikka masala was tasting like a tomato soup. No go for us.
I love this place!!  Amazing Indian food, highly affordable. Service could be improved. Highly recommend for any day of the week.

Very well organised and welcoming restaurant. They serve generous portions and for economical prices. I enjoyed the meals very much and the staff members were very attentive and chatty. I recommend this place.
Solid Indian food.
Decent taste but does not meet the expectation as boasted by the owner of the restaurant.
Flawless service, tasty food and nice atmosphere. We took the buffet option and it did not disappoint. They genuinely care for you to have a great experience. We will be coming back for more!
Spicy food and good
Wonderful service, many veggie options, and impeccable food and drink.

Great place!!! The food is amazing. If you stay or are ever in the Lincoln park area please stop by you will not be disappointed. The owner and staff is wonderful,  very nice and friendly, recommends great selections to pair with your dinner. The vegetable samosas are delicious!!! I ordered the Fish curry, fresh and packed with the perfect amount of spices. There are some many delicious items on the menu you will not go wrong with everything you order. We traveled from the south suburbs to this place and we love it!!!!
Absolutely delicious food. Made fresh & in good quantity. Very satisfied. Looking forward to visit again soon.
One of my favorite restaurants in Chicago. The Chana masala is the BEST I’ve had. Love bringing friends and family here, always a favorite with everyone. Amazing vegetarian and vegan options
Came here on a Friday I think. Definitely worth a return visit.
Excellent and very very delicious Indian Food, I have ever ate here in Chicago. Very calm n friendly atmosphere. I recommend Raj Darbar Indian Restaurant for delicious n tasty Indian food.

We live in the Lincoln Park neighborhood.  This is one of our favorite restaurants to either eat-in or to order takeout.  The food is flavorful, fresh, and pleasingly presented.  Service is consistently friendly and efficient. A pleasant dining experience guaranteed to meet expectations.
This place was over-the-top amazing. My friend has lived in India for 4 years, and he said it was some of the best food he's ever had.
Very rude service, mediocre food
Tasty Indian Asian food
Samosa 🏅
Good food ruined by rude service.
Had takeout, samosas were great, decent everything else... did have an upset stomach after & not the only one.
The chicken biryani was next level delicious. Will definitely be back
My favorite Indian restaurant. We order from here often no matter  where we move to
Fantastic. The various naans alone are worth a visit.

HORRIBLE experience. Ordered delivery on their website (had already ordered via their website before) and never received anything. However, I did get charged the almost $50. I called the restaurant many times and left two voicemails, emailed the restaurant, and they never returned my call. I tried calling again and the main manager was extremely rude.  Never ordering from here ever again. The food is bad, the management is horrendous.
Good food and hospitality
A good selection of Indian favorites. Friendly and casual.
Both the food and service is bad. I did a mistake, went by using Groupon coupon.
Mediocre food, average service. Much better options in the local area, like Ghareeb Nawaz

If I lived closer I’d go often. It’s the best Indian restaurant in the area, hands down. It’s a little campy, but it’s night at night with large booths for friends. Everything I’ve had has been excellent. I find it’s best to go later, so it’s dark and noisy. It’s awkwardly quiet in the early evening.
Good food and quick service! The mango lassi and curry lamb was delicious!
Delicious, quality food and nice people.
Best channa masala around.
I'm soory but plz don't eat here I got here at 1020. With plenty of time to eat but they closed early so I had to change plans.
Reasonable food. A little overpriced. The ambience needs work.
Food and service was good.

Please save your money. The service is worst. The waitera are rude and dont know the basics of hospitality. Unfortunately, the food is also just like their service. Biryani is nothing more than a peas pulao and all curries no matter what have the same tomate base and they all taste the same. we ordered chicken do pyaza, chicken jalferazi and paneer makhani and they all tasted the same. Don't waste your time and money. I wish I could give them negative rating.  There are many other Indian restaurant with better food and a better service.  I

Large menu featuring all your favorites plus house specialties.  In addition to naan and garlic naan, I recommend the onion naan. The vegetarian dishes are very good as are the lamb, shrimp and chicken dishes. The rice is perfect. I often get their takeout too. When we're had a large group,  they do a great job of serving everyone.
Good food. Worst service. There was no a/c at all when complained, the manager acted as if he doesn't know and did nothing about it. Till our 5th complain.

I dined in at Raj for the first time last night and had a phenomenal experience. Who I suspect to be the owner, as well as the whole staff, was very pleasant and made our dinner great. While I do not know the Indian cuisine that well, I do know good food, which is what Raj was full of.  I would recommend Raj to anyone.

Excellent traditional Indian food. Exceptionally flavorful and seasoned. Good non, if you are a non fan. Excellent service, very friendly, owner comes out and asks you how you are enjoying things. A small wine selection, however their selection compliments their food quite well. A true gem.
Order from the clay oven section of the menu 🔥🔥🔥
Interesting

Best Indian food in the area! Butter chicken, rice, spinach, simosas, naan, garlic naan, and bryani were amaaaaaazing. Had it delivered and came right on schedule. The flavors were amazing. I'm not a fan of Indian food, but it was super delicious.
Good food, decent service.  All in all just good but not good enough to be memorable or great.
Excellent food, great for take out
Food taste was not good.
Pretty good food and atmosphere. It's never busy, so it's a pretty quiet place for your eating needs.
Courteous service, elegant presentation. Mutter paneer was well seasoned but the cheese lacked the toasted firmness I expect from the dish. Definitely a buy!

Food and service rather bizarrely poor. Baingan eggplant dish was heavily Americanized combo with midwestern brown sauce.  Tandoori chicken appeared boiled,  not baked, equally pedestrian sauce.  Server neglected to ask how spicy we wanted it;  it came out not spicy at all. Service?  Terrible.  We had a flight the next morning and it took 25 minutes twiddling our thumbs to get a check and leave.  Maybe the owner has a half hour to sit around doing nothing,  we didn't.

Pretty good South Asian fare without the trek to Rogers Park. Very good tandoori dishes, with vegetarian options. The gravy based dishes are on the rich side. We opted for medium heat, which was just right.
They have cockroaches in the kitchen.
Good ambiance
Never fails. Raj Darbar special enough to feed an army.

Place is solid. Love their food.  Their staff is super friendly, and the last time I was there we came in close to close...prime time for employees to not give you great service. They were just as welcoming and friendly as always, and our food came out perfect.
You have to go there to enjoy it! Nice setup.

Absolutely awful. I will never buy from these guys again - it took an hour and 45 minutes for my food to arrive and when it did it was stone cold. I had to microwave it, if I wanted a microwave meal I'd have gone to Walmart! Called the restraint to complain, it went to voicemail, left a message nobody ever called me back. I paid $60 for absolute rubbish. Clearly the price is no indication of quality here.
Indian restaurant  very nice seatting good food

Can't comment on the food, but they advertise having a Sunday Lunch Buffee from 11-2:30 on their coupons... which is not the case.  The sign said open at 1:30 PM, but it was dark inside and they didn't have any customers.  The host told us that they did not have a lunch buffet on Sunday's, so they have already lost a potential customer b/c of their false advertising.  Might want to fix the error on their advertisements if they don't want to disappoint other customers.
Food was amazing.

The food here was really good.  I most enjoyed the palak paneer with spinach and ate it with naan.  The samosas were so crispy and flavorful and less greasy than others I've had.  The chicken tikka masala wasn't anything too amazing, but we enjoyed the lamb in a rice dish.  This was definitely a good place to come for Indian food.  It took a while to get our bill, but it wasn't a huge deal.
Very low-key restaurant. A perfect spot to get a great and casual dinner with friends and family. The staff are all very friendly and the food is always delicious!
So so. Malai Kofta could've been a lot more batter

Good food! But the service was absolutely terrible. We waited half an hour for the waiter to take our order, I never received the smoothie I ordered (they charged me for it, but then took off the charge once I talked to them), and they gave me a different tandoori dish than I had ordered. We ended up being there for two and a half hours, simply because we were waiting on our food... we ate the meal within 20 minutes. The food was pretty good, but the service made it a very bad experience.

Visited this on Labor Day weekend, service was courteous. We ordered Paneer Do Pyaza and Daal Makhni along with butter Naan.  Dishes served were doing justice to themselves. Also the Naans were one of the finest I have eaten at quite a few Indian restaurants. Altogether nice choice for authentic taste.

The food here is pretty decent. I actually came here with my girlfriend not too long ago with a groupon. You can get sooooo much food here, it is ridiculous. I myself can eat a lot of food and even after getting a few drinks, we still had food to last us for days.
Raj Darbar isn't worth trying out.  The food is dry, prices are high, and the place just feels dirty.  For good Indian food nearby, try Tandoor a few doors down.

They have the best tandoori chicken ever. So flavorful and juicy! Oh, their lamb lamb vindaloo is soo good, tender and lots of flavor as well. Honestly, I wish I was as excited about going to others restaurants as I am about going to Raj Darbar. You guys rock!
I can't testify to the authenticity, but the food was amazing!  I got the chicken tika masala with the garlic naan and a mango lassi. Everything was delicious!!

To make it quick: The food was great. My friend and I ordered chana masala with roti. I ordered an extra order of papadum, but never received it. I wasn't charged for it so, no harm no foul.  Our waiter was okay. He took quite a bit of time to take our order and my friend pretty much had to stop him and ask him if we could order. The place wasn't busy, mind you. It was around 9:45 on a Saturday night and they close at 11.  When we received our roti, I noticed it looked at as if had butter on it. I've been to other Indian restaurants and never received butter on my roti. I asked the waiter if the roti did in fact have butter on it and he said yes. I asked for an order of roti without butter. Here comes the fun part: I'm basically politely lectured that all Indian restaurants put butter on their roti, I can have anything customizable, and I basically should have said I didn't want butter. I had a college reading level when I was in middle school. I love to read. I read the menu and didn't see butter listed anywhere on the description for roti.  So, the waiter brings my roti and has to comment, "Here is your roti WITHOUT BUTTER." I gave my friend a look to convey, "No he didn't."  In summary: The food is good, but the service leaves a bit to be desired. If you have time to wait for your order or for your bill OR you're assertive, this is the place for you. I'm not sure if I'll be back considering Chicago has a lot of Indian restaurants.
We ate veg and chicken biryani. Not up to the mark. If you are expecting some thing like Hyderabady biryani, its not for you. North Indians may like the taste.

This place is really good food. I really like the bases for the curries they make - that's what makes the food taste amazing. Once a michillin bib restuarant, they haven't lost their finesse. I wouldn't get the biryani though, as it was my least favorite thing there. The service sometimes leave a little to be desired, as there seems little communication between the kitchen and front of house.

I must have ordered delivery from this place at least 30 times if not more, and I have never been disappointed. I've never been inside, so my "Good" rating for decor is a wild guess. But if you want Indian food delivered to your door, I don't think it's possible to do better than Raj Darbar. Everything is good. They have a bunch of different types of naan, which is somewhat unusual. I like it, the potato filled one and the garlic are both great. Also love the samosas and chicken tikka masala. The epitome of consistency.

Awesome Sunday Buffet. I love the Paneer and the Chicken Pakora which are fried in chickpea batter. They have a great assortment of Naans, with beef, assorted nuts and all kinds of spices. Order something from the clay oven,  I love their tandori chicken it is so flavorful!
Very good Indian food at a reasonable price. Host was extremely attentive. I recommend the Chicken Tikka Masala.
